.TH BOTTOM 1 "2026-07-10" "bottom 0.1.1" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
bottom \- record process lifecycle events
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B bottom
[
.I options
]
.br
.B bottom
.I command
[
.I options
]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B bottom
is a read-only process lifecycle recorder. It records process starts, executable replacements, stops, restart churn, and detected capture gaps. Recordings can be queried, replayed, summarized, compared, and exported as a Perfetto timeline.
.PP
With no command, bottom behaves like
.BR "bottom record" .
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B record
Record lifecycle events. This is the default command.
.TP
.B watch
Alias for
.BR record .
.TP
.B trace
Start one command directly and record it and its observed descendants. Options must precede an exact
.B --
separator.
.TP
.B query
Filter one or more SQLite recordings and render text, JSONL, or CSV.
.TP
.B replay
Replay one or more SQLite recordings with merged timing or through the terminal interface.
.TP
.B report
Summarize sessions, event kinds, gaps, failures, process groups, ancestry, and lifetimes across recordings.
.TP
.B compare
Compare process groups, ancestry, failures, counts, and lifetimes in two SQLite recordings.
.TP
.B version
Print version, source commit, and build date.
.TP
.B completion
Write fish completions to standard output. Save the output as
.IR ~/.config/fish/completions/bottom.fish .
.SH OPTIONS
Every option has a documented default and usage description. Run
.B bottom -h
for recording options or
.B bottom command -h
for command-specific options.
.PP
The
.B -input
option may be repeated up to 64 times for query, replay, and report. Events are merged by time, sequence, and input order. Without this option, those commands read
.IR bottom.sqlite .
.SH RECORDING FORMATS
Text output is intended for terminals. JSONL and CSV contain versioned session, event, and gap records. SQLite schema version 4 supports indexed queries, replay, reports, and comparisons.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I bottom.sqlite
Default SQLite recording path.
.TP
.I bottom-trace.sqlite
Default trace recording path.
.TP
.I ~/.config/fish/completions/bottom.fish
Fish completion installation path.
.SH SECURITY
bottom observes processes but does not act on them. New recording files request owner-only access. Use repeated
.B -redact
options to replace exact sensitive values before recording.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR ps (1),
.BR sqlite3 (1)
